  "title": "Desecrated Deck",
  "description": "Desecrated Deck is a dark card game set in a cursed cellar where every move teeters between life and death. Use mystical perks and fate-driven cards to strike deadly pacts, defeat your opponent, and survive the malevolent forces – or be claimed by darkness.",
  "longDescription": "<!--textBlock-->\n<!--text-->\nEnter a haunted world in Desecrated Deck, a card game set in a cursed cellar where every decision is a step closer to survival…or demise. Use fate-driven items-cards and eerie perk-cards, and watch as your choices become both your strength and potential downfall.\n\nGameplay Mechanics\n\nDesecrated Deck combines the intensity of rock-paper-scissors with a dark twist. Players battle with powerful Item-Cards, drawn based on the winner of each round’s rock-paper-scissors throw, bringing a blend of strategy and chance that makes every game unique.\n\nItem-Cards\n\nEach of the 6 Item-Card has a unique effect. The Revolver poses a brutal threat, stripping an opponent’s life with a single shot—if it fires. Alternatively, the Pest Doctor grants a vital reprieve, restoring one life to its user. Every card has a risk and a reward, heightening the tension as you wait to see what fate has drawn.\n\nPerk-Cards\n\nStrategically use Perk-Cards to defend yourself or throw your opponent off-balance. These cards grant eerie powers that manipulate Item Card outcomes, counter attacks, or weaken your opponent's chance of success. Perks range from The Poisoned Mushroom, which sabotages attacks, to The Cursed Mirror, reflecting an opponent’s power back at them.\n\nAtmosphere and Visuals\n\nWith dark, atmospheric graphics and immersive sound effects, Desecrated Deck draws players into an unsettling experience. The game’s horror-inspired visuals are accentuated by haunting audio, binaural sounds, and eerie visuals that bring each card's malevolent spirit to life.\n\nWill you brave the Desecrated Deck, or will the darkness claim you?\n\nSystemanforderungen\n",
